# Models

Serialised model artefacts are not included in this repository
due to file size. Follow the steps below to regenerate them.

---

## How to Regenerate Models

### Step 1 — Download Data
Follow instructions in `data/README.md` to download the
DEFRA CSV file and place it in the `/data` folder.

### Step 2 — Run Training Pipeline
```bash
python src/train_model.py
```

This will automatically generate all model artefacts
in this `/models` folder.

---

## Generated Files

| File | Description | Algorithm |
|---|---|---|
| `rf_model.pkl` | Trained Random Forest classifier | Ensemble |
| `xgb_model.pkl` | Trained XGBoost classifier | Gradient Boosting |
| `lstm_model.h5` | Trained LSTM deep learning model | Deep Learning |
| `label_encoder.pkl` | AQI category label encoder | Preprocessing |
| `location_encoder.pkl` | City name label encoder | Preprocessing |
| `scaler.pkl` | MinMaxScaler for LSTM input | Preprocessing |
| `feature_cols.pkl` | Feature column list | Preprocessing |

